text.section:
The County Commissioners of St. Mary's County may regulate any public road, street, avenue, lane, alley or bridge, sidewalk, curb, gutter, and storm drainage facilities within St. Mary's County which is not within the corporate limits of any incorporated city or town and which has not been designated or maintained as a part of the State or federal highway system or any extension with respect to:
The weight of vehicles;
The parking of vehicles;
The abandonment of vehicles;
Use by private and public utilities in the construction and maintenance necessitated by the performance of their purpose;
The construction and maintenance of driveway connections where those connections are provided; and
The speed of vehicles.
